    "body": "## Goal\nAdd the no-key, default training data source: a loader for the CC0 `martj42/international_results` datasets that fetches `results.csv`, `shootouts.csv`, and `goalscorers.csv`, coerces them to the internal schema, normalizes team names, and validates the exact data-contract shapes. martj42 alone provides every nation's history **and** the WC2026 schedule, so this must run with zero API key.\n\n## Context\n**Data contract (verified 2026-06-23):** base URL `https://raw.githubusercontent.com/martj42/international_results/master/`.\n- `results.csv` \u2014 **49,477 rows**, source cols `date, home_team, away_team, home_score, away_score, tournament, city, country, neutral`. `home_score`/`away_score` are the string `\"NA\"` for unplayed fixtures \u2192 coerce to nullable `Int64`. `neutral` is the string `\"TRUE\"`/`\"FALSE\"` \u2192 parse to `bool`. WC2026 fixtures are already present as `tournament == \"FIFA World Cup\"` with `NA` scores until played and `neutral == TRUE`.\n- `shootouts.csv` \u2014 **678 rows**: `date, home_team, away_team, winner, first_shooter`.\n- `goalscorers.csv` \u2014 **47,741 rows**: `date, home_team, away_team, team, scorer, minute, own_goal, penalty`.\n\n**Internal target schema for results:** `DATE, HOME_TEAM, AWAY_TEAM, HOME_GOALS (Int64), AWAY_GOALS (Int64), TOURNAMENT, NEUTRAL (bool)`.\n\n**Critical integration detail:** the existing validator in `worldcup_playoff/data/loader.py` (`_validate_dataframe`, `REQUIRED_*_COLUMNS`) only treats `{int64,float64,int32,float32}` and `{object,str,string}` as compatible dtype families \u2014 it does **not** accept nullable `Int64` or `bool`. Do **not** reuse `REQUIRED_MATCHES_COLUMNS` (that is the football-data.org `MATCH_ID/COMPETITION/SEASON` shape). Define new `REQUIRED_MARTJ42_*` dicts and a martj42-local validator that extends the family logic to `Int64` and `bool`. This is the single highest-risk detail.\n\n**`FootballClient` cannot help here** \u2014 it is hardwired to the football-data.org v4 base URL, so martj42 must fetch via `pd.read_csv(url)`. Use a cache-first design (read local cache file if present, else download and write cache) so tests and no-key runs stay fully offline and deterministic.\n\nConventions: module `\"\"\"docstring\"\"\"` \u2192 `from __future__ import annotations` \u2192 `logger`; pair the loader class with thin module-level `load_martj42_*` factory functions (mirrors `build_*_csv` / `generate_bracket_toml`). Pydantic config models use `ConfigDict(extra=\"ignore\")` and compose onto `AppConfig` in `config.py`.\n\n## Agent and skills\n- **Agents:** `python-pro`\n- **Active skills:** `solid-principles`, `python-expert`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] `Martj42Loader.load_results()` returns a DataFrame with exactly `DATE, HOME_TEAM, AWAY_TEAM, HOME_GOALS, AWAY_GOALS, TOURNAMENT, NEUTRAL`; `\"NA\"` scores become `<NA>` in `Int64` columns; `\"TRUE\"`/`\"FALSE\"` become real `bool`\n- [ ] `load_shootouts()` and `load_goalscorers()` return their contract schemas (`WINNER/FIRST_SHOOTER`; `TEAM/SCORER/MINUTE/OWN_GOAL/PENALTY`)\n- [ ] Team-name columns (`HOME_TEAM`, `AWAY_TEAM`, and `TEAM` for goalscorers) pass through `normalize_team`/`normalize_series` from the crosswalk\n- [ ] New `REQUIRED_MARTJ42_*_COLUMNS` dicts + `validate_results_df`/`validate_shootouts_df`/`validate_goalscorers_df` wrappers; the martj42 validator accepts `Int64` and `bool` and raises `ValueError` (same \"missing column\"/\"wrong dtype\" contract as `loader.py`) on bad frames\n- [ ] Cache-first: no network read when the cache file exists; `Martj42Config` added to `config.py` and composed onto `AppConfig`; `dataset/martj42/*.csv` added to `.gitignore`\n- [ ] A `wc2026_schedule()` convenience filter returns `tournament == \"FIFA World Cup\"` rows including unplayed (`<NA>`-score) fixtures\n- [ ] Schema-verification tests assert the exact data-contract dtypes/columns; network is mocked (fixture CSV in `tmp_path` as cache, or patch `pd.read_csv`) \u2014 no real HTTP; the existing 250-test suite stays green\n- [ ] All tests pass\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- #1: feat: team-name crosswalk for martj42 \u2194 football-data.org normalization\n\n## Implementation notes\n- **Create:** `worldcup_playoff/data/martj42_loader.py` \u2014 `Martj42Loader` (`__init__(config, cache_dir=None, base_url=None)`, `load_results/load_shootouts/load_goalscorers/wc2026_schedule`), private `_fetch_raw` (cache-first `pd.read_csv`), `_coerce_results` (`pd.to_numeric(..., errors=\"coerce\").astype(\"Int64\")` for scores; `{\"TRUE\":True,\"FALSE\":False}` map for `NEUTRAL`), `_apply_crosswalk`; the `REQUIRED_MARTJ42_*` dicts + `validate_*_df` wrappers + a local `_validate_martj42` extending `loader.py`'s family sets; module-level `load_martj42_results/_shootouts/_goalscorers` factories.\n- **Create:** `tests/test_martj42_loader.py` \u2014 fixture CSVs (a dozen rows incl. a `\"NA\"` score, `\"TRUE\"`/`\"FALSE\"` neutral, a `T\u00fcrkiye` row) loaded from a `tmp_path` cache; assert `df[\"HOME_GOALS\"].dtype == \"Int64\"` and `df[\"NEUTRAL\"].dtype == bool`; assert crosswalk applied and the WC2026 filter behavior.\n- **Modify:** `worldcup_playoff/config.py` \u2014 add `Martj42Config(BaseModel)` (`base_url`, `cache_dir=\"dataset/martj42\"`, `results_file/shootouts_file/goalscorers_file`) and wire `martj42: Martj42Config = Martj42Config()` onto `AppConfig`.\n- **Modify:** `worldcup_playoff/data/__init__.py` \u2014 export `Martj42Loader`, the `load_martj42_*` factories, `REQUIRED_MARTJ42_*`, validators; extend `__all__`. **Modify:** `.gitignore` \u2014 add `dataset/martj42/*.csv`.\n- Reuse `loader.py`'s `_validate_dataframe` only for the string/object columns; never hit the network in tests; do not modify `REQUIRED_MATCHES_COLUMNS`.",
