t_dixon_coles` once; pass both into the historical builder and `wc2026_features`; assert the two frames share the **same column set** and the WC2026 frame's rows are a subset of the historical frame's rows. Runs with **no network**.\n- [ ] Full suite (existing + new) stays green; `ruff check` (line-length 100) and `mypy --strict` are clean on the new package.\n- [ ] All tests pass\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- #7: feat: static confederation map + FIFA-ranking fallback resolver + [features_build] config\n- #8: feat: time-aware recent-form, rest-days, and goal-difference helpers\n- #9: feat: core per-match feature assembler over martj42 history\n- #10: feat: WC2026 current-state feature frame\n\n## Implementation notes\n- **Modify:** `worldcup_playoff/features/__init__.py` \u2014 populate the export surface with an `__all__` list (mirroring `simulation/__init__.py`):\n  - From `confederation`: `CONFEDERATIONS`, `CONFEDERATION_MAP`, `confederation_of`, `resolve_ranking`, `RankingResolution`.\n  - From `timeaware`: `sort_chronological`, `recent_form`, `rest_days`, `goal_difference`.\n  - From `build`: `MatchFeatures`, `FeatureBuilder`, `build_features`, `to_frame`.\n  - From `wc2026`: `wc2026_features`, `live_fixtures_to_df`.\n- **Create:** `tests/test_features_integration.py` \u2014 the no-key end-to-end smoke test described above; in-memory frames only, no network/I/O; assert same-column-set between historical and WC2026 frames and the subset relationship.\n- Conventions: `from __future__ import annotations`; explicit imports + sorted `__all__`; no globals; mypy strict; ruff line-length 100. Do not pre-wire pipeline/CLI.",
