    "body": "## Goal\nBuild the pure, stateless helpers that compute the **strictly pre-match** time-dependent covariates \u2014 time-weighted recent form, rest days, and windowed goal difference \u2014 over a chronologically sorted match frame. Isolating these as pure functions makes the **no-forward-leakage** guarantee unit-testable in isolation, independent of Elo/Poisson. These are leaf functions consumed by the core assembler.\n\n## Context\nCycle 3 assembles per-match football-only covariates time-aware (a match's features may use only information available **strictly before** that match). The cleanest leakage guarantee is to anchor the whole builder to **one chronological sort** that is byte-identical to the Elo engine's sort, so each helper can read only rows with `index < before_idx`.\n\nKey facts:\n- `worldcup_playoff/data/elo.py` sorts internally by `[\"_d\", \"HOME_TEAM\", \"AWAY_TEAM\", \"HOME_GOALS\", \"AWAY_GOALS\"]` with `kind=\"stable\"`, `na_position=\"last\"`, then `reset_index(drop=True)` (where `_d = pd.to_datetime(df[\"DATE\"], errors=\"coerce\")`). Your `sort_chronological(df)` must **reproduce this exact key** so the sorted frame is positionally aligned 1:1 with `EloResult.match_diffs` (which the sibling assembler consumes).\n- Input frame schema (from `Martj42Loader.load_results()`): `DATE` (object ISO string), `HOME_TEAM`/`AWAY_TEAM` (normalized object), `HOME_GOALS`/`AWAY_GOALS` (nullable `Int64`, `<NA>` for unplayed incl. WC2026), `TOURNAMENT` (object), `NEUTRAL` (bool).\n- Reuse the existing decay primitive `decay_weight(age_days, half_life_days)` from `worldcup_playoff/simulation/poisson.py` (`0.5 ** (age/half_life)`) \u2014 do NOT redefine it.\n- `FeatureBuildConfig` (form_window, form_half_life_days, random_seed) comes from issue #7.\n\n**Scope guard:** pure compute only \u2014 no Elo/Poisson recompute (Cycle 2 consume), no per-match assembly (sibling task), no model/training (Cycle 4), no Monte Carlo (Cycle 5).\n\n## Agent and skills\n- **Agents:** `python-pro`\n- **Active skills:** `solid-principles`, `python-expert`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] `sort_chronological(df)` reproduces the Elo engine's sort key exactly (stable, `na_position=\"last\"`, reset index) \u2014 verified against a constructed frame.\n- [ ] `recent_form` for a team with a single prior 3-0 win returns the max decayed points-per-game; with no prior matches returns a defined neutral default (e.g. `0.0`) \u2014 pick one and assert it.\n- [ ] **No-leakage:** inserting a *later* match into the frame does not change `recent_form(before_idx=i)` for an earlier `i` (explicit test);... [truncated, 10310 bytes omitted]` — JSON array of Phase 1 issues, each with `issue_number`, `title`, `body`, `labels`
