  {
    "body": "## Goal\nCreate the shared, dependency-light foundation both Cycle-4 models build on: a time-aware (chronological, no-shuffle) match-dataset utility that derives goal-based targets, plus the `HybridConfig` and `OrderedLogitConfig` Pydantic models wired into `AppConfig` and `config/default.toml`. A single source of truth for target derivation and the chronological split prevents the two models from drifting apart.\n\n## Context\nCycle 4 adds a primary goal-based RF/GBM hybrid and a secondary Elo-diff ordered logit. Both consume the Cycle-3 covariate frame from `worldcup_playoff/features/build.py`: `build_features(df, elo, abilities, ...)` returns a DataFrame with `FEATURE_COLUMNS` = (date, home_team, away_team, neutral, home_elo, away_elo, elo_diff, home_attack, home_defence, away_attack, away_defence, home_form, away_form, home_rest_days, away_rest_days, home_goal_diff, away_goal_diff, home_confederation, away_confederation, home_ranking, away_ranking, home_goals, away_goals) plus a `tournament` column.\n\n- `home_goals`/`away_goals` are `Int64` nullable (NA for unplayed WC2026 fixtures); confederation columns are categorical strings; `home_ranking`/`away_ranking` and `*_rest_days` are nullable.\n- The frame is already chronologically sorted by `sort_chronological` (`features/timeaware.py`), which shares its sort key with the Elo engine (`data/elo.py` `SORT_COLS`).\n- The legacy trainer already establishes the no-shuffle convention: `models/classifiers.py:71` uses `train_test_split(..., shuffle=False)`. Do NOT modify `classifiers.py` (kept as the backtest baseline).\n- All config is Pydantic sub-configs aggregated on `AppConfig` (`config.py:288-300`) and mirrored as TOML tables in `config/default.toml`. `statsmodels` is not yet a dependency (added in a sibling task).\n\n## Agent and skills\n- **Agents:** `python-pro`\n- **Active skills:** `solid-principles`, `python-expert`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] `outcome_label(home_goals, away_goals)` returns the ordered encoding away-win=0 < draw=1 < home-win=2.\n- [ ] `add_targets(df)` returns a copy adding `y_outcome` (Int64, values in {0,1,2}) and `y_margin` (= home_goals \u2212 away_goals) for group goal-difference tiebreaks.\n- [ ] `played_only(df)` drops rows where `home_goals` or `away_goals` is NA.\n- [ ] `chronological_split(df, test_size=...)` is positional/no-shuffle: `train.date.max() <= test.date.min()`, deterministic (no RNG), never reorders.\n- [ ] `build_dataset(features, test_size, feature_cols)` returns a frozen `MatchDataset(train, test, feature_cols)` with played-only, disjoint train/test rows.\n- [ ] `AppConfig` exposes `.hybrid` (HybridConfig) and `.ordered_logit` (OrderedLogitConfig) with documented defaults; `config/default.toml` has matching `[hybrid]`/`[ordered_logit]` tables; `load_config` round-trips overrides.\n- [ ] All tests pass\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- none (foundation task)\n\n## Implementation notes\n- **Create:** `worldcup_playoff/models/dataset.py` \u2014 frozen `MatchDataset` dataclass + module-level pure helpers `outcome_label`, `add_targets`, `played_only`, `chronological_split`, `build_dataset`. Pure pandas/numpy only \u2014 no sklearn/statsmodels import, so it stays fast to test. Re-assert order with `from worldcup_playoff.features.timeaware import sort_chronological` before splitting (self-defensive). Test slice = last `floor(n*test_size)` rows; purely positional \u2192 deterministic with no `random_state`.\n- **Modify:** `worldcup_playoff/config.py:262-300` \u2014 add `HybridConfig` (e.g. `rf_n_estimators: int = 300`, `rf_max_depth: int | None = None`, `gb_n_estimators: int = 200`, `gb_learning_rate: float = 0.05`, `max_goals: int = 10`, `rho: float = -0.1`, `test_size: float = 0.2`, `random_seed: int = 42`; `ConfigDict(extra=\"ignore\")`; validator `0 < test_size < 1`) and `OrderedLogitConfig` (`features: list[str] = [\"elo_diff\"]`, `maxiter: int = 100`, `test_size: float = 0.2`, `random_seed: int = 42`). Wire `hybrid: HybridConfig = HybridConfig()` and `ordered_logit: OrderedLogitConfig = OrderedLogitConfig()` into `AppConfig`.\n- **Modify:** `config/default.toml` \u2014 append `[hybrid]` and `[ordered_logit]` tables mirroring the defaults (the \"stub config needed to fit\" permitted this cycle; final command surface is Cycle 5).\n- **Create:** `tests/test_models_dataset.py` \u2014 assert encoding, NA-drop, chronological split (no leakage + determinism), target columns. Build in-memory feature frames following the `_matches`/`_elo`/`TeamAbilities` pattern in `tests/test_features_build.py`.\n- **Modify:** `tests/test_config.py` \u2014 assert `.hybrid`/`.ordered_logit` defaults, TOML round-trip, and the `test_size` validator rejects 0 and 1.\n- Conventions: frozen dataclass value objects, module-level pure helpers + a thin class, deterministic seeds, mypy strict, ruff line-length 100.",
