    "body": "## Goal\nEnd-to-end no-key wiring and verification capstone: from a martj42 fixture, compute Elo \u2192 fit Dixon-Coles abilities \u2192 `build_features` \u2192 `build_dataset` \u2192 fit BOTH new models, asserting they produce valid probabilistic output, are deterministic, and coexist with the retained legacy SVM/RF/NB baseline. This locks in the cycle acceptance criterion \"the full pipeline runs no-key (martj42 + computed Elo/Poisson features)\" and that the existing suite stays green.\n\n## Context\nMirrors the Cycle-3 capstone (issue #11, \"features package public API + no-key integration smoke test\"). This task adds NO new model logic \u2014 it is pure integration verification. The pieces it ties together:\n- `worldcup_playoff/data/elo.py` `compute_elo` \u2192 `EloResult`.\n- `worldcup_playoff/simulation/poisson.py` `fit_dixon_coles` \u2192 `TeamAbilities`.\n- `worldcup_playoff/features/build.py` `build_features(df, elo, abilities, ...)` \u2192 covariate frame.\n- `worldcup_playoff/models/dataset.py` `build_dataset` \u2192 `MatchDataset` (from #12).\n- `worldcup_playoff/models/hybrid.py` `fit_hybrid` (from #13) and `worldcup_playoff/models/ordered_logit.py` `fit_ordered_logit` (from #14).\n- Legacy `ClassifierFactory`/`ClassifierTrainer`/`ModelEvaluator` (`models/classifiers.py`, `models/evaluation.py`) remain the backtest baseline ONLY \u2014 do NOT modify them; just confirm they still construct.\n\nThe whole path must run without a `FOOTBALL_DATA_API_KEY` (martj42 CC0 data + computed Elo/Poisson features only). The current suite collects 711 tests; all must remain green.\n\n## Agent and skills\n- **Agents:** `python-pro`\n- **Active skills:** `solid-principles`, `python-expert`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] A no-key end-to-end test fits both new models from a martj42 fixture through `compute_elo` \u2192 `fit_dixon_coles` \u2192 `build_features` \u2192 `build_dataset`.\n- [ ] Hybrid output: predicted goals `>= 0` and W/D/L probabilities sum to 1.\n- [ ] Ordered-logit output: W/D/L probabilities sum to 1.\n- [ ] Re-fitting both models with the same seed yields identical predictions (determinism).\n- [ ] `ClassifierFactory.create` still builds the `svm`/`random_forest`/`naive_bayes` baselines (baseline coexistence).\n- [ ] `worldcup_playoff.models` re-exports the full Cycle-4 surface alongside the legacy exports.\n- [ ] The full existing suite stays green (`pytest`).\n- [ ] All tests pass\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- #13: feat: Groll-style RF/GBM goal-based hybrid model (primary predictor)\n- #14: feat: Elo-diff ordered logit secondary model (statsmodels)\n\n## Implementation notes\n- **Create:** `tests/test_models_integration.py` \u2014 build a small in-memory/fixture martj42 results frame, run the full no-key path, and assert the criteria above. Reuse fixture patterns from `tests/test_features_build.py` and `tests/conftest.py`; keep each test focused (one behavior per test).\n- **Verify (modify only if a gap remains):** `worldcup_playoff/models/__init__.py` exposes `HybridGoalModel`, `GoalPrediction`, `fit_hybrid`, `OrderedLogitModel`, `OutcomeProbabilities`, `fit_ordered_logit`, `MatchDataset`, `build_dataset` plus the legacy `ClassifierFactory`/`ClassifierTrainer`/`ModelEvaluator`.\n- Run `pytest` to confirm the existing 711 tests remain green after the additive Cycle-4 modules land.\n- No new CLI commands, no Monte-Carlo simulation, no scoring/backtest harness, no odds \u2014 those are Cycle 5.\n- Conventions: deterministic seeds, mypy strict, ruff line-length 100.",
