    "body": "## Goal\nImplement the cycle's primary predictor: a Groll-Ley-Zeileis style Random-Forest / Gradient-Boosting hybrid (arXiv 1806.03208) that consumes Poisson attack/defence abilities + Elo + Cycle-3 covariates to predict per-match goals (home & away), then derives a W/D/L distribution and goal margin from the predicted goal pair. Goal-based by design so it preserves goal margin for group goal-difference tiebreaks and naturally models draws.\n\n## Context\nConsumes the feature frame from `worldcup_playoff/features/build.py` (`FEATURE_COLUMNS` + `tournament`): numeric covariates `home_elo, away_elo, elo_diff, home_attack, home_defence, away_attack, away_defence, home_form, away_form, home_rest_days, away_rest_days, home_goal_diff, away_goal_diff, home_ranking, away_ranking`; categorical `home_confederation, away_confederation, neutral`; targets `home_goals, away_goals` (Int64). The shared `worldcup_playoff/models/dataset.py` (dependency) provides the chronological no-shuffle `MatchDataset` and target derivation.\n\nReuse the already-tested \u03c4-corrected Poisson machinery to turn predicted goal means into outcome probabilities: `worldcup_playoff/simulation/poisson.py` exposes `score_matrix(lh, la, rho, max_goals)` and `dixon_coles_tau`. Summing the lower / diagonal / upper triangles of the score matrix gives `(prob_home, prob_draw, prob_away)` that sum to 1 by construction. `TeamAbilities` (attack/defence/home_adv/rho/intercept) come in via the feature frame's `*_attack`/`*_defence` columns. The model must satisfy the spirit of the `Classifier` Protocol (`types.py`) but is goal-regression-based, not a binary classifier.\n\n## Agent and skills\n- **Agents:** `python-pro`\n- **Active skills:** `solid-principles`, `python-expert`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] Output is goal-based: `predict_goals` returns expected (home, away) goals, all clipped `>= 0`.\n- [ ] `predict` returns `GoalPrediction` records with `prob_home + prob_draw + prob_away == 1` (within tol), each in [0,1], plus `margin = home_goals \u2212 away_goals`.\n- [ ] W/D/L is derived via the reused `simulation.poisson.score_matrix` (proper simplex, non-zero draw mass).\n- [ ] Time-aware: `fit` trains on `MatchDataset.train` only \u2014 never re-splits or shuffles.\n- [ ] Deterministic: two fits with the same `random_seed` produce identical predictions (`np.allclose`).\n- [ ] Design matrix excludes `home_goals`/`away_goals`/`date`/`home_team`/`away_team` (no target or identity leakage) and contains no NaN columns; runs no-key.\n- [ ] All tests pass\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- #12: feat: time-aware match dataset utility + Hybrid/OrderedLogit config models\n\n## Implementation notes\n- **Create:** `worldcup_playoff/models/hybrid.py` \u2014 `GoalPrediction` frozen dataclass; module-level helpers `build_design_matrix(df)` and `derive_outcome_probs(lh, la, *, max_goals, rho)`; thin `HybridGoalModel` class (`__init__(config: HybridConfig)`, `fit(dataset) -> Self`, `predict_goals(df) -> np.ndarray` shape (n,2), `predict(df) -> list[GoalPrediction]`); `fit_hybrid(features, config)` factory. Keep the class < 50 lines \u2014 push logic to module-level pure helpers.\n- Use `RandomForestRegressor` + `GradientBoostingRegressor` (one pair per goal target, or RF+GB blended), both seeded with `config.random_seed`; pin `n_jobs=1` on RF for reproducibility; clip predicted goals to `>= 0`.\n- `derive_outcome_probs` must reuse `from worldcup_playoff.simulation.poisson import score_matrix` (do not re-derive the pmf grid).\n- Encode confederations with a FIXED category ordering from `worldcup_playoff/features/confederation.py` `CONFEDERATION_MAP` (not data-dependent `OneHotEncoder` discovery), so unseen WC2026 confederations don't break inference. Impute nullable `*_rest_days`/`*_ranking` with a fit-time fixed sentinel (e.g. train median or 0) decided at fit and stored \u2014 never recomputed at predict (no leakage).\n- **Modify:** `worldcup_playoff/models/__init__.py` \u2014 export `HybridGoalModel`, `GoalPrediction`, `fit_hybrid` (additive; keep legacy baseline exports).\n- **Create:** `tests/test_hybrid_model.py` \u2014 assert probs sum to 1 and within [0,1]; symmetric inputs \u2192 near-equal home/away probs; goals `>= 0`; determinism on re-fit; design-matrix leakage exclusion; trains on `dataset.train` only. Build in-memory frames via the `tests/test_features_build.py` fixture pattern.\n- Conventions: frozen dataclass value objects, DI of config, deterministic seeds, mypy strict, ruff line-length 100.",
