    "body": "## Goal\nAdd Ranked Probability Score (RPS, primary), multiclass log-loss, and Brier score on time-aware splits, then backtest the hybrid model on WC2014/2018/2022 \u2014 reporting metrics **vs the scraped bookmaker baseline** and **vs the legacy classifier**. Accuracy (hybrid RPS \u2248 or below the bookmaker baseline) is THE acceptance criterion of the whole cycle.\n\n## Context\n`models/evaluation.py` (68 lines) currently only has `ModelEvaluator.evaluate()` (confusion matrix + classification report, `evaluation.py:21-35`) and `plot_roc_curves()`. It needs probabilistic W/D/L metrics.\n\nInputs available:\n- `models/hybrid.py` `HybridModel.predict(features) -> GoalPrediction` (`hybrid.py:179-181`) yields `prob_home/prob_draw/prob_away`; `fit_hybrid(dataset, config)` builds it. `GoalPrediction` (`hybrid.py:44-53`).\n- `models/dataset.py` `chronological_split(df, test_size)` (`dataset.py:105-123`, no-shuffle, deterministic) and `build_dataset(...)` give time-aware splits; `outcome_label(home_goals, away_goals)` (`dataset.py:59-65`) maps to 0=away/1=draw/2=home.\n- `models/classifiers.py` legacy SVM/RF/NB classifier as the second baseline.\n- The de-vigged bookmaker probabilities come from `data/odds.py` (issue #20) \u2014 baseline only, never a feature.\n\nW/D/L is a 3-class ordinal outcome \u2192 RPS is the appropriate primary metric (cumulative squared error over ordered classes). Time-aware splits only: never shuffle chronological data. Backtest must still run if odds are missing (degrade gracefully \u2014 report hybrid vs legacy and skip the bookmaker column).\n\n## Agent and skills\n- **Agents:** `python-pro`\n- **Active skills:** `solid-principles`, `python-expert`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] Pure metric functions added: `rank_probability_score` (ordered 3-class), `multiclass_log_loss`, `brier_score` (3-class W/D/L) \u2014 each unit-tested against hand-computed values on tiny known arrays.\n- [ ] A `backtest_hybrid` orchestrator slices played WC matches per tournament-year (2014/18/22) on time-aware splits, predicts W/D/L with the hybrid, and returns a comparison table vs the bookmaker baseline (from #20) and vs the legacy classifier.\n- [ ] RPS is reported as the primary metric; log-loss and Brier reported alongside.\n- [ ] Backtest degrades gracefully when odds are unavailable (skips the bookmaker column, still compares hybrid vs legacy).\n- [ ] All tests pass; new `tests/test_evaluation_metrics.py` (exact metric values) and `tests/test_backtest.py` (synthetic 2-tournament frame, stub hybrid + stub odds \u2192 comparison table).\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- #16: feat: Cycle 5 config groundwork \u2014 [rf]/[odds] sections, knockout sim params, TOML wiring\n- #20: feat: archived bookmaker odds scraper + de-vig + CSV cache (data/odds.py)\n\n## Implementation notes\n- **Modify:** `worldcup_playoff/models/evaluation.py` \u2014 add the three pure metric functions (keep them small and import-light). If adding the backtest orchestration would push the file past ~500 lines, **Create:** `worldcup_playoff/models/backtest.py` for the `backtest_hybrid` orchestration and keep only the metrics in `evaluation.py`.\n- **Create:** `tests/test_evaluation_metrics.py` \u2014 assert exact RPS/log-loss/Brier on hand-computed arrays.\n- **Create:** `tests/test_backtest.py` \u2014 synthetic frame + stub hybrid/odds \u2192 assert the comparison table shape and the graceful-no-odds path.\n- Consume `chronological_split`/`build_dataset` from `models/dataset.py` \u2014 never shuffle. Bookmaker odds are a baseline only, never passed into model features.",
