    "body": "## Goal\nRun ~100,000 seeded Monte-Carlo tournaments (group-stage simulation + knockout) conditioned on played WC2026 results, and aggregate per-team **title odds** plus **per-round advancement probabilities** for all 48 teams. This is the central integration node that produces the live forecast.\n\n## Context\nThis orchestrator wires together the Cycle-5 simulation pieces:\n- `data/live.py` `fetch_tournament_state(client=None, competition=\"WC\")` (`live.py:151-158`) returns a `TournamentState` (played / remaining_group_fixtures / standings). It must run **no-key by default** \u2014 when no API key is present, fall back to the martj42 WC2026 schedule (martj42 already contains WC2026 fixtures with `tournament == \"FIFA World Cup\"`). The football-data.org key only refines live state.\n- `simulation/poisson.py` `fit_dixon_coles(df, config)` \u2192 `TeamAbilities`; `make_sampler(abilities, config)` \u2192 `ScorelineSampler` (`poisson.py:264-271`). Fit once on historical martj42 data, then reuse across all simulations.\n- The group-stage simulator (issue #17) produces final v4-shaped standings; the knockout simulator (issue #18) resolves R32 from those standings and folds to a champion.\n- `simulation/tournament.py` `RoundResult` (`tournament.py:31-61`) exposes `.probabilities = {team: count / n_simulations}` \u2014 reuse this contract so the plotter (issue #23) can consume per-round results unchanged.\n\nPerformance target: ~100k tournaments complete in seconds\u2013low minutes. Determinism: a master seed derives per-iteration sub-seeds so two runs with the same seed produce identical odds.\n\n## Agent and skills\n- **Agents:** `python-pro`\n- **Active skills:** `solid-principles`, `python-expert`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] Orchestrates: ingest `TournamentState` \u2192 fit/accept `TeamAbilities` once \u2192 loop N tournaments (group sim from #17 + knockout from #18) with per-iteration sub-seeds derived from a master seed \u2192 accumulate champion + round-reached counts.\n- [ ] Returns a `ForecastResult` value object with full title odds (champion probability per team, all 48 teams present) and `{round: probabilities}` per-round advancement reusing the `RoundResult.probabilities` contract.\n- [ ] Title-odds across all 48 teams sum to \u2248 1.0; per-round advancement counts match the number of slots in each round.\n- [ ] Runs **no-key by default** (martj42 WC2026 schedule); football-data.org key optional for live refinement; re-runnable after each matchday.\n- [ ] Deterministic: same master seed \u2192 identical odds across two runs.\n- [ ] ~100k tournaments complete in seconds\u2013low minutes (document the measured timing).\n- [ ] All tests pass; new `tests/test_live_forecast.py` runs a small-N forecast with a stub sampler asserting probability sanity, 48-team coverage, and seed reproducibility.\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- #16: feat: Cycle 5 config groundwork \u2014 [rf]/[odds] sections, knockout sim params, TOML wiring\n- #17: feat: group-stage simulation engine with FIFA tiebreaks (simulation/group_stage.py)\n- #18: feat: R32 resolution + single-elimination knockout sim with extra-time/penalties (simulation/knockout.py)\n\n##... [truncated, 16393 bytes omitted]` — JSON array of Phase 1 issues, each with `issue_number`, `title`, `body`, `labels`
