    "body": "## Goal\nScrape archived WC2014/2018/2022 outright + match odds, de-vig them to probabilities, and cache to CSV \u2014 used **only** as the backtest baseline to beat (never a model feature). Must degrade gracefully so a blocked source never breaks the forecast.\n\n## Context\nThe evaluation/backtest task (issue #21) needs a de-vigged bookmaker probability baseline. Odds source: per the data contract, historical **World Cup** outright/match odds (2014/18/22) must be scraped from archived sources (oddsportal/web-archive) and cached; de-vig is `p_i = (1/o_i) / \u03a3(1/o_j)`.\n\nResilience is a hard requirement: scrapers are fragile, so the loader must be **cache-first** and **never raise** into the forecast/eval path \u2014 a 403/blocked source falls back to the cached CSV (or an empty frame), never an exception. Mirror the cache-first pattern already used by `data/martj42_loader.py` (`Martj42Loader._fetch_raw`). Config comes from the new `[odds]` section (issue #16): `cache_dir`, `seasons`, source URL(s), `request_timeout`, `user_agent`, `enabled`/fallback flags.\n\n`pyproject.toml` currently lists deps `numpy, pandas, scikit-learn, scipy, statsmodels, fitter, matplotlib, requests` (lines 13-21) \u2014 **`beautifulsoup4` is missing** and must be added for HTML parsing. Team names must be normalized via `data/crosswalk.normalize_team` so odds rows join to historical/forecast team names.\n\n## Agent and skills\n- **Agents:** `python-pro`\n- **Active skills:** `solid-principles`, `python-expert`\n\n## Acceptance criteria\n- [ ] `OddsScraper` (or loader functions) fetches archived WC2014/18/22 outright + match odds and parses them with BeautifulSoup.\n- [ ] De-vig implemented as `p_i = (1/o_i) / \u03a3(1/o_j)`; resulting probabilities per market sum to 1.0.\n- [ ] Cache-first: results written to / read from CSV under `[odds].cache_dir`; a cached read needs no network.\n- [ ] Graceful degradation: a blocked/raising source falls back to cache (or empty frame) and **never** propagates an exception.\n- [ ] Team names normalized via `crosswalk.normalize_team`.\n- [ ] `beautifulsoup4` added to `pyproject.toml` dependencies.\n- [ ] All tests pass; new `tests/test_odds.py` parses saved HTML fixtures (no live network), asserts de-vig sums to 1.0, and asserts a simulated 403/exception triggers cache/empty fallback without raising.\n- [ ] SOLID, clean code (methods < 10 lines, classes < 50 lines, files < 500-600 lines), TDD\n\n## Dependencies\n- #16: feat: Cycle 5 config groundwork \u2014 [rf]/[odds] sections, knockout sim params, TOML wiring\n\n## Implementation notes\n- **Create:** `worldcup_playoff/data/odds.py` \u2014 `OddsScraper` with cache-first read/write, per-source `try/except` \u2192 cache/empty fallback, de-vig helper, and crosswalk normalization. Consume `AppConfig.odds`.\n- **Modify:** `pyproject.toml:13-21` \u2014 add `beautifulsoup4>=4.12` to `dependencies`.\n- **Modify:** `worldcup_playoff/data/__init__.py` \u2014 export the public scraper/loader entry point.\n- **Create:** `tests/test_odds.py` \u2014 fixture HTML strings parsed offline; de-vig math; blocked-source fallback. Do NOT hit live network in tests.\n- Bookmaker odds are an evaluation baseline ONLY \u2014 do not feed them into `features/build.py` or `models/hybrid.py`.\n- Verify nothing here breaks no-key default operation: odds are optional; absence must not break the forecast.",
